motypic synonym is <em>Rhodobium marinum</em> (Imhoff, 1984) Hiraishi et al. 1995, comb. nov. <a href="#bib11">[11]</a>.</s></p><p class="description"><s>The description is identical to that given for <em>Rhodobium marinum</em> by Hiraishi et al. <a href="#bib11">[11]</a>.</s><s>The type strain shares the characteristics listed in the genus description.</s><s>The type strain is DSM 2898<sup>T</sup> (=BN 126=ATCC 35675=CIP 104405=NBRC 100434).</s></p></content></protolog>